ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: When my child misbehaves:
Notes: 1= I do something right away; 7= I do something later

ElementDescription: Before I do something about a problem:
Notes: 1= I give my child several reminders and warnings; 7= I use only one reminder and warning

ElementDescription: When I'm upset or under stress:
Notes: 1= I am picky and on my child's back; 7= I am not more picky than usual

ElementDescription: When I tell my child NOT to do something:
Notes: 1= I say very little; 7= I sat a lot

ElementDescription: When my child pesters me:
Notes: 1= I can ignore the pestering; 7= I can't ignore the pestering

ElementDescription: When my child misbehaves:
Notes: 1= I usually get into a long argument with my child; 7= I don't get into an argument

ElementDescription: I threaten to do things that:
Notes: 1= I'm sure I can carry out; 7= I know I won't actually do

ElementDescription: I am the kind of parent that:
Notes: 1= Sets limits on what my child is allowed to do; 7= Lets my child do whatever he/she wants

ElementDescription: When my child misbehaves:
Notes: 1= I give my child a long lecture; 7= I keep my talks short and to the point

ElementDescription: When my child misbehaves:
Notes: 1= I raise my voice or yell; 7= I speak to my child calmly

ElementDescription: If saying no doesn't work right away:
Notes: 1= I take some other kind of action; 7= I keep talking and try to get through to my child

ElementDescription: When I want my child to stop doing something:
Notes: 1= I firmly tell my child to stop; 7= I coax or beg my child to stop

ElementDescription: When my child is out of sight:
Notes: I often don't know what my child is doing; 7= I always have a good idea of what my child is doing

ElementDescription: After theres been a problem with my child:
Notes: 1= I often hold a grudge; 7= Things get back to normal quickly

ElementDescription: When we're not at home:
Notes: 1= I handle my child the way I do at home; 7= I let my child get away with a lot more

ElementDescription: When my child does something I don't like:
Notes: 1= I do something about it every time it happens; 7= I often let it go

ElementDescription: When there is a problem with my child:
Notes: 1= Things build up and I do things I don't mean to do; 7= Things don't get out of hand

ElementDescription: When my child misbehaves I spank, slap, grab, or hit my kid:
Notes: 1= Never or rarely; 7= Most of the time

ElementDescription: When my child doesn't do what I ask:
Notes: 1= I often let it go or end up doing it myself; 7= I take some other action

ElementDescription: When I give a fair threat or warning:
Notes: 1= I often don't carry it out; 7= I do what I said

ElementDescription: If saying no doesn't work:
Notes: 1= I take some other kind of action; 7= I offer my child something nice so he/she will behave

ElementDescription: When my child misbehaves:
Notes: 1= I handle it without getting upset; 7= I get so frustrated or angry that my child can see I'm upset

ElementDescription: When my child misbehaves:
Notes: 1= I make my child tell me why he/she did it; 7= I say "no" or take some other action

ElementDescription: If my child misbehaves and then acts sorry:
Notes: 1= I handle my problem like I usually would; 7= I let it go that time

ElementDescription: When my child misbehaves:
Notes: 1= I rarely use bad language or curse; 7= I almost always use bad language

ElementDescription: When I say my child can't do something:
Notes: 1= I let my child do it anyway; 7= I stick to what I said

ElementDescription: When I have to handle a problem:
Notes: 1= I tell my child I'm sorry about it; 7= I don't say I'm sorry

ElementDescription: When my child does something I don't like, I insult my child, say mean things, or call my child names:
Notes: 1= Never or rarely; 7= Most of the time

ElementDescription: If my child talks back or complains when I handle a problem:
Notes: 1= I ignore the complaining and stick to what I said; 7= I give my child a talk about not complaining

ElementDescription: If my child gets upset when I say "no":
Notes: 1= I back down and give in to my child; 7= I stick to what I said
